Package: CountNA
Title: Count Missing Values for all Columns by Group
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Sarah", 
            family = "Masri", 
            role = c("aut", "cre"),
            email = "sarah.masri@student.ubc.ca")
Description: Given a data frame `data` and a column `group`, 
    `count_all_missing_by_group()` creates a new data frame with one row 
    per level of `group`. The first column of the output data frame contains the 
    levels of `group`, and the rest of the columns contain the number of missing values for
    all columns in `data` except `group`.
